The paper discusses a low-cost strategy for predicting the accuracy of artificial neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning and specifically deep learning. The paper also applies this strategy to hyper-parameter optimization, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
